{
  "stem": "5911.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was on a list.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we also met more friends, and they told us in detail that he gave up completely.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's when we found out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't want to live.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He died in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When they were also marching out of Dachau, he died in 22 days in Tavid.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It came out in January of 1945.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Can you imagine the irony of all this?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He died in the same month that we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I didn't know the exact month.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Years later in Montreal, it was-- I found out that he died on the way somewhere in 22 days in Tavid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And again, I had my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I suppose, life goes on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we tried to get into a DP camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that must have been the time already when they put-- we got to Bad Gastein, and we got to Bad Gastein in November in 1945.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A large-- wandering.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wandering around.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Wandering around like the wandering Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Wandering around trying to find-- that was the objective of mostly everybody, to find relatives.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe, maybe, maybe one person-- my mother had a big family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "OK, my father's family emigrated, but my mother had a big family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where was-- there was nobody left.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my aunt's sons were grown.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were grown.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My mother was the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It means she was the youngest one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So maybe one survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had come to Russia, had five sons, and [INAUDIBLE] had also, had four children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She was, I think, next to my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That everybody that was-- like we were-- we thought-- we-- we found out going towards Lithuania, going towards Kaunas.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that for sure, we found out in Lodz that nobody survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Upon discovered, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
